 Business Briefs
																								 New Delhi, Nov. 7: The government will jointly allocate two coal blocks in Orissa to six companies, including Reliance Energy and gmr, to meet the fuel requirements of their proposed power plants. The coal ministry has offered Rampia and the dip side of Rampia blocks with gross reserves of 645 million tonnes. The four other companies are Sterlite Energy, Mittal Steel, Lanco Group and Navbharat Power Pvt Ltd.																								 New Delhi, Nov. 7: The Central Electricity Regulatory Commission has proposed a revenue-sharing mechanism for the use of transmission assets by power utilities for telecom business at an annual charge of Rs 3,000 per km.																								 Calcutta, Nov. 7: HDFC Bank has got the RBIs approval to set up a non-banking finance company. The first line of recruitment (of chief executive officer and other higher officials) have been done, said Pralay Mondal, country head (retail assets and credit cards), HDFC Bank.																								 Mumbai, Nov. 7: Hindalco Industries will seek shareholders approval for the merger of Indian Aluminium Company Ltd with itself on November 12.																								 Paris, Nov. 7: ArcelorMittal will invest $647 million to pick up a 28 per cent stake in China Oriental. The transaction will make ArcelorMittal the second-largest shareholder in the Chinese firm.
